\c 36
\s1 Tanah Bagi Anak-Anak Peremuan Zelafehad
\p Pemimpin-pemimpin tiap kaum/marga Gilead dari The family leaders of the cenghadap Musa/aku dan beberapa kaum keluarga orang Israel.
\v 2 They said to Moses/me, “Yahweh commanded you, our leader, to apportion the land to the Israeli tribes by throwing◄lots/stones that have been marked► to decide \add which group would get whicharea\add*. Yahweh also commanded you to give the land that belonged to our fellow Israeli Zelophehad to his daughters.
\v 3 But if his daughters marry men from the other Israeli tribes, that land will no longer belong to our tribe. People of other tribes will get it. So some of our land will no longer belong to us.
\v 4 When the Year of Celebration comes, \add when all the land that has been bought by someone is returned to its originalowners\add*, the land that belonged to Zelophehad will belong to the tribes of the men that his daughters marry. So some of our land, the land that we received from our fathers, will be taken from us,\add and we will never own it again\add*.”
\p
\v 5 Tuhan berkata/berfirman kepadaku/Musa supaya mengatakan demikian kepada bangsa Israel: “Orang-orang dari kaum/suku keturunan Manasye itu benar/jujur.
\v 6 Inilah perkataan/firman yang diperintahkan Tuhan tentang anak-anak perempuan Zelafehad: ‘Mereka boleh kawin dengan siapa saja yang mereka mau, tetapi/asalkan masih ada dalam kaum dari suku/keturunan ayah mereka.’
\v 7 In that way, the land that belongs to Israelis will not be passed from one tribe to another tribe. Each Israeli will keep the land in the tribe that belonged to his ancestors.
\v 8 A woman who inherits her father's land may get married, but she must marry someone from her own tribe. In that way, every Israeli will keep the land that belonged to his ancestors.
\v 9 The land must not be passed from one tribe to another tribe. Each Israeli tribe must keep the land that it received from its ancestors.”
\p
\v 10 Anak-anak perempuan dari Zelefehad melakukan segala sesuatu seperti yang diperintahkan Musa kepada mereka/aku perintahkan kepada mereka.
\v 11 Kelima anak perempuanya yaitu-Mahlah, Tirza, Hoglah, Milca and Noa—mereka ini menikah dengan anak-anak laki-laki dari keluarga ayah mereka.
\v 12 Mereka menikah/kawin dengan laki-lki sei kaum keluarga Manasye, yaitu anak daru Yusuf, sehingga tanah pusaka/tanah itu tetap menjadi milik turun-temurun/melajutkan kepunyaan keluarga ayah mereka.
\p
\v 13 Itulah selruh perintah dan hukum yang diberikan TUhan kepada Musa/aku unutk disampaikan kepada seluruh bangsa Israel ketika mereka melewati daratan Moab, di dekat Sungai Yordan sebelah/di depan Kota Yerikho.